    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Gray or bluish cloud sheets or layers of striated or fibrous clouds that totally or partially covers the sky. They are thin enough to regularly reveal the sun as if seen through ground glass. Altostratus clouds do not produce a halo phenomenon nor are the shadows of objects on the ground visible.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
